import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['year'] = pd.to_datetime(data['year'], format='%Y', errors='coerce')
    fig, ax = plt.subplots()
    ax.scatter(data['miles'], data['gas'])
    ax.set_xlabel('Miles Driven')
    ax.set_ylabel('Gas Consumption')
    plt.title('What is the relationship between miles driven and gas consumption?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['miles'].plot(kind='hist', bins=20, color='blue', edgecolor='black')
    plt.axvline(data['miles'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=2, label='Mean')
    plt.axvline(data['miles'].median(), color='green', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=2, label='Median')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of miles driven?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['year'] = pd.to_datetime(data['year'], format='%Y', errors='coerce')
    data = data.sort_values(by='year')
    plt.plot(data['year'], data['miles'])
    plt.title('What is the trend in miles driven over time?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['year'] = pd.to_datetime(data['year'], format='%Y', errors='coerce')
    data = data.sort_values(by='year')
    plt.plot(data['year'], data['gas'])
    plt.axhline(y=data['gas'].mean(), color='r', linestyle='-')
    plt.title('What is the trend in gas consumption over time?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Year')
    plt.ylabel('Gas Consumption')
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
